# Application Layer -- AuntiesRecipe.Application

The contract layer. Defines **what** the system can do without specifying **how**.

## Project References

- `AuntiesRecipe.Domain` -- ONLY allowed reference

## Allowed

- Service interfaces in `Abstractions/` (e.g., `ICartService`, `IOrderService`)
- DTOs as `sealed record` types organized by feature folder (Cart/, Orders/, Menu/, Business/)
- Mapping extension methods that convert Domain entities → DTOs (if kept static and pure)
- Enums or constants that define application-level concerns (not domain-level)

## Forbidden

- Any concrete class that implements a service interface (those belong in Infrastructure)
- `using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore` or any ORM reference
- `using Microsoft.AspNetCore.*` or any web/HTTP reference
- References to `AuntiesRecipe.Infrastructure` or `AuntiesRecipe.Web`
- Direct I/O of any kind

## Conventions

- **One DTO file per feature folder**: `Cart/CartDtos.cs`, `Orders/OrderDtos.cs`, etc.
- **Sealed records for DTOs**: Immutable, clear contracts.
- **Interface naming**: `I{Feature}Service` in `Abstractions/`.
- **Method signatures use DTOs**, not Domain entities, for inputs/outputs to higher layers.

## Examples

```csharp
// GOOD -- clean interface contract
namespace AuntiesRecipe.Application.Abstractions;

public interface ICartService
{
    Task<CartDto?> GetCartAsync(string cartId);
    Task AddItemAsync(string cartId, int menuItemId, int quantity);
    Task<OrderSummaryDto> CheckoutAsync(string cartId, CheckoutRequestDto request);
}

// BAD -- leaking Infrastructure types
using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore;

public interface ICartService
{
    Task<CartDto?> GetCartAsync(string cartId, AppDbContext db);
}
```

## Adding a New Service Contract

1. Create `I{Feature}Service.cs` in `Application/Abstractions/`
2. Create `{Feature}Dtos.cs` in `Application/{Feature}/` with sealed record DTOs
3. Implement the interface in `Infrastructure/Services/{Feature}Service.cs`
4. Register in `Infrastructure/DependencyInjection.cs`
